-- FESCO Transportation Group Posts $63.6 Million First-Half Loss
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-08-30T04:30:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-30/fesco-transportation-group-posts-63-6-million-first-half-loss.html
FESCO Transportation Group, the
largest shipping company in  Russia ’s far east, swung to a loss
in the first half of this year because of asset impairment and
higher costs, according to a  report  on the company’s website.  Net loss attributable to shareholders was $63.6 million
compared to $38.2 million profit a year earlier, while sales
rose 27 percent to $582.5 million, according to the website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
